aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aFrom objects to sounds, choreography is expanding beyond dance and human bodies in motion. This book offers one of the rare systematic investigations of expanded choreography as it develops in contemporaneity, and is the first to consider expanded choreography from a trans-historical perspective. Through case studies on different periods of European dance history - ranging from Renaissance dance to William Forsythe's choreographic objects and from Baroque court ballets to digital choreographies - it traces a journey of choreography as a practice transcending its sole association with dancing, moving, human bodies.  afunded by Austrian Science Fund - FWF (Fonds zur Förderung der wissenschaftlichen Forschung)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aChoreography. 4aCultural History. 4aCulture. 4aDance. 4aEuropean Choreography. 4aTheatre Studies. 4aTheatre. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Dance / General.2bisacsh  aChoreography.  aCultural History.  aCulture.  aDance.  aEuropean Choreography.  aTheatre Studies.  aTheatre.2 aAustrian Science Fund - FWF (Fonds zur Förderung der wissenschaftlichen Forschung)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2022z9783110992809oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2022 Englishz978311099281608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 E